Route Priority - Exam Important! ğŸ¯
Jab multiple matching routes hon, to MOST SPECIFIC (longest prefix) win karta hai:

Example Route Table:
10.0.0.0/16    â†’  Local
10.0.1.0/24    â†’  NAT-Gateway
0.0.0.0/0      â†’  Internet-Gateway

Traffic to 10.0.1.50:
âœ… Match: 10.0.1.0/24 (most specific) â†’ NAT Gateway use hoga
âŒ Not used: 10.0.0.0/16 (less specific)
âŒ Not used: 0.0.0.0/0 (least specific)

Priority Order: /32 > /24 > /16 > /8 > /0

Common Exam Questions Pattern:
Question Type 1: Troubleshooting
Q: EC2 instance internet access nahi kar pa raha. Kya check karoge?

Answer checklist:
1. âœ… Route table mein 0.0.0.0/0 â†’ igw-xxx hai?
2. âœ… Subnet us route table se associated hai?
3. âœ… Security Group outbound allow hai?
4. âœ… NACL outbound allow hai?
5. âœ… Instance mein public IP/Elastic IP hai?
Question Type 2: Best Practice
Q: Database servers ke liye konsa routing setup best hai?

Answer:
- Private subnet mein rakho
- Route table: 0.0.0.0/0 â†’ NAT Gateway
- Direct internet access NAHI
- Outbound updates/patches ke liye NAT use karo
Question Type 3: Cost Optimization
Q: Multiple private subnets hai, kaise cost optimize karoge?

Answer:
- Ek hi NAT Gateway multiple private subnets ke liye
- Sab private route tables mein same NAT Gateway point karo
- Multiple NAT Gateways sirf HA ke liye (multi-AZ)

Important Exam Points - Yaad Rakho! ğŸ“

âœ… Har subnet ko ek route table chahiye (explicitly ya default)
âœ… Local route automatically hai - delete nahi kar sakte
âœ… 0.0.0.0/0 â†’ IGW = Public subnet
âœ… 0.0.0.0/0 â†’ NAT = Private subnet
âœ… Most specific route wins (longest prefix match)
âœ… Ek route table = multiple subnets possible
âœ… Ek subnet = ek route table (at a time)
âœ… Default route table modify kar sakte ho, delete nahi
âœ… Route propagation VPN/Direct Connect ke liye auto routes
âœ… Edge Association - Internet Gateway level routing
